{"word":"Μίνως","slug":"Μίνως","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Μίνως</b></el> <p/><i>Minos</i>, son of Zeus and Europa, king of Crete, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <el>Μίνωος</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <el>Μίνωα</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>;—also <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <el>Μίνω</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <el>Μίνων</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, or <el>Μίνω</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <el>Μίνῳ</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/>"}]}